            <scopecontent id="aspace_994a2a3f798310494917c1307ac26055">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The series holds letters sent to Adella Fowler Larkin by members of her family, including her sisters Almira and Ella, stepbrother George Pratt, aunt Sarah, and various cousins. Prominent among them are nine folders of letters sent by Myra Fowler McFarland from her teaching positions in Florida, South Carolina, and Georgia before, during, and immediately after the Civil War. Her last folder holds nine episodes of the "Milwaukee Bad Boy" stories by George W. Peck clipped from an unidentified newspaper. Also notable are Pratt's letters which encouraged James and Adella Larkin to join him in Wisconsin, as well as those of his visiting mother, Ann R. Fowler, which describe family matters and her views of life in Wisconsin.</p>
            </scopecontent>
